               <p>ROBERT OWENS. I am a <rs id="t18180617-94-viclabel519" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180617-94-victim814 t18180617-94-viclabel519"></join>. I was working at a new building at the corner of <placeName id="t18180617-94-crimeloc520">Balsover-street, Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180617-94-crimeloc520" type="placeName" value="Balsover-street, Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180617-94-crimeloc520" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180617-94-off517 t18180617-94-crimeloc520"></join> - I went to breakfast at eight o'clock. The prisoner was brought to the public-house with the tools.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180617-94-person815">
                  WILLIAM 
                  LINFIELD
               <interp inst="t18180617-94-person815" type="surname" value="LINFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180617-94-person815" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180617-94-person815" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a bricklayer. I saw the prisoner standing in the middle of the street - I suspected him, and crossed the street; he went into the building, and came out again. I crossed over, secured him, and found the hammer and chisel under his coat.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found them.</p>
